    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Its not exactly elegant, but if you use List.listIterator(int index) you can get a bi-directional ListIterator to the end of the list:</p>\n<pre><code>//Assume List&lt;String&gt; foo;\nListIterator li = foo.listIterator(foo.size());\n\nwhile (li.hasPrevious()) {\n   String curr = li.previous();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
