    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1759550073,
    "last_edit_date" : 1759550073,
    "creation_date" : 1682676342,
    "answer_id" : 76128465,
    "question_id" : 3962766,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2><code>SequencedCollection#reversed</code></h2>\n<p>Since Java 21 there is a new interface <a href=\"https://openjdk.org/jeps/431\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>SequencedCollection</code></a> (which is a superinteface for <code>List</code>). It has the method <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/SequencedCollection.html#reversed()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>reversed()</code></a> which provides a reverse-ordered view of a collection:</p>\n<pre><code>jshell&gt; List.of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5).reversed()\n$1 ==&gt; [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]\n</code></pre>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://openjdk.org/jeps/431\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em>JEP 431</em></a> and <a href=\"https://youtu.be/6yuDqkkYTGU\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">video</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 249565,
        "reputation" : 11314,
        "user_id" : 525725,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 67,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8304c64641badd4218a89a5f97d2ae86?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Emmanuel Bourg",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/525725/emmanuel-bourg"
      },
      "edited" : false,
