    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since Java 21 use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/List.html#reversed()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>List.reversed</code></a>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Returns a reverse-ordered view of this collection. The encounter order\nof elements in the returned view is the inverse of the encounter order\nof elements in this collection. The reverse ordering affects all\norder-sensitive operations, including those on the view collections of\nthe returned view. If the collection implementation permits\nmodifications to this view, the modifications &quot;write through&quot; to the\nunderlying collection. Changes to the underlying collection might or\nmight not be visible in this reversed view, depending upon the\nimplementation.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So you have a reversed view of the original list.</p>\n"
  } ],
